4096 
4097  /// \short Use finite differences to calculate the Jacobian entries
4098  /// corresponding to the solid positions.
4099  void fill_in_jacobian_from_solid_position_by_fd(DenseMatrix<double> &jacobian)
4100  {
4101  //Allocate storage for a residuals vector and initialise to zero
4102  unsigned n_dof = ndof();
4103  Vector<double> residuals(n_dof,0.0);
4104  //Get the residuals for the entire element
4105  get_residuals(residuals);
4106  //Call the jacobian calculation
4107  fill_in_jacobian_from_solid_position_by_fd(residuals,jacobian);
4108  }

4179  /// \short Access to the "multiplier" for the

4182  inline double multiplier(const Vector<double>& xi)
4183  {

4186  {

4189  else

4202  //========================================================================
4203  /// FaceElements are elements that coincide with the faces of
4204  /// higher-dimensional "bulk" elements. They are used on
4205  /// boundaries where additional non-trivial boundary conditions need to be
4206  /// applied. Examples include free surfaces, and applied traction conditions.
4207  /// In many cases, FaceElements need to evaluate to quantities
4208  /// in the associated bulk elements. For instance, the evaluation
4209  /// of a shear stresses on 2D FaceElement requires the evaluation
4210  /// of velocity derivatives in the associated 3D volume element etc.
4211  /// Therefore we store a pointer to the associated bulk element,
4212  /// and information about the relation between the local
4213  /// coordinates in the face and bulk elements.
4214  //========================================================================
4215  class FaceElement: public virtual FiniteElement
4216  {
4217  /// \short Typedef for the function that translates the face coordinate
4218  /// to the coordinate in the bulk element
4219  typedef void (*CoordinateMappingFctPt)(const Vector<double> &s,
4220  Vector<double> &s_bulk);
4221 
4222  /// \short Typedef for the function that returns the partial derivative
4223  /// of the local coordinates in the bulk element
4224  /// with respect to the coordinates along the face.
4225  /// In addition this function returns an index of one of the
4226  /// bulk local coordinates that varies away from the edge
4227  typedef void (*BulkCoordinateDerivativesFctPt)(
4228  const Vector<double> &s, DenseMatrix<double> &ds_bulk_dsface,
4229  unsigned &interior_direction);
4230 
4231  private:
4232 
4233  /// \short Pointer to a function that translates the face coordinate
4234  /// to the coordinate in the bulk element
4235  CoordinateMappingFctPt Face_to_bulk_coordinate_fct_pt;
4236 
4237  /// \short Pointer to a function that returns the derivatives of the local
4238  /// "bulk" coordinates with respect to the local face coordinates.
4239  BulkCoordinateDerivativesFctPt Bulk_coordinate_derivatives_fct_pt;
4240 
4241  /// \short Vector holding integers to translate additional position types
4242  /// to those of the "bulk" element; e.g. Bulk_position_type(1) is
4243  /// the position type of the "bulk" element that corresponds to face position
4244  /// type 1. This is required in QHermiteElements, where the slope in the
4245  /// direction of the 1D element is face position type 1, but may be
4246  /// position type 1 or 2 in the "bulk" element, depending upon which face,
4247  /// we are located.
4248  Vector<unsigned> Bulk_position_type;
4249 
4250  /// \short Sign of outer unit normal (relative to cross-products of tangent
4251  /// vectors in the corresponding "bulk" element.
4252  int Normal_sign;
4253 
4254  /// \short Index of the face
4255  int Face_index;
4256 
4257  /// \short Ignores the warning when the tangent vectors from
4258  /// continuous_tangent_and_outer_unit_normal may not be continuous
4259  /// as a result of the unit normal being aligned with the z axis.
4260  /// This can be avoided by supplying a general direction vector for
4261  /// the tangent vector via set_tangent_direction(...).
4262  static bool Ignore_discontinuous_tangent_warning;
4263 
4264  protected:
4265 
4266  /// The boundary number in the bulk mesh to which this element is attached
4267  unsigned Boundary_number_in_bulk_mesh;
4268

4272  /// compiled with PARANOID switched on.
4273  bool Boundary_number_in_bulk_mesh_has_been_set;
4274 
4275 #endif

4278  FiniteElement* Bulk_element_pt;
4279 
4280  /// \short List of indices of the local node numbers in the "bulk" element
4281  /// that correspond to the local node numbers in the FaceElement
4282  Vector<unsigned> Bulk_node_number;
4283 
4284  /// \short A vector that will hold the number of data values at the nodes that
4285  /// are associated with the "bulk" element. i.e. not including any additional

4287  /// that are being solved by

4289  // NOTE: This breaks if the nodes have already been resized

4299  Vector<double>* Tangent_direction_pt;
4300 
4301  /// \short Helper function adding additional values for the unknowns
4302  /// associated with the FaceElement. This function also sets the map
4303  /// containing the position of the first entry of this face element's
4304  /// additional values.The inputs are the number of additional values
4305  /// and the face element's ID. Note the same number of additonal values
4306  /// are allocated at ALL nodes.
4307  void add_additional_values(const Vector<unsigned> &nadditional_values,
4308  const unsigned &id)
4309  {
4310  // How many nodes?
4311  const unsigned n_node=nnode();
4312 
4313  // loop over the nodes
4314  for (unsigned n=0; n<n_node; n++)
4315  {
4316  //Assign the required number of additional nodes to the node
4317  dynamic_cast<BoundaryNodeBase*>(
4318  this->node_pt(n))->assign_additional_values_with_face_id(
4319  nadditional_values[n],id);
4320  }
4321  }

4509  /// \short Set the tangent direction vector.
4510  void set_tangent_direction(Vector<double>* tangent_direction_pt)
4511  {
4512 #ifdef PARANOID
4513  // Check that tangent_direction_pt is not null.
4514  if (tangent_direction_pt == 0)
4515  {
4516  std::ostringstream error_message;
4517  error_message
4518  << "The pointer tangent_direction_pt is null.\n";
4519  throw OomphLibError(error_message.str(),
4520  OOMPH_CURRENT_FUNCTION,
4521  OOMPH_EXCEPTION_LOCATION);
4522  }
4523 
4524  // Check that the vector is the correct size.
4525  // The size of the tangent vector.
4526  unsigned tang_dir_size = tangent_direction_pt->size();
4527  unsigned spatial_dimension = this->nodal_dimension();
4528  if (tang_dir_size != spatial_dimension)
4529  {
4530  std::ostringstream error_message;
4531  error_message
4532  << "The tangent direction vector has size " << tang_dir_size << "\n"
4533  << "but this element has spatial dimension " << spatial_dimension
4534  << ".\n";
4535  throw OomphLibError(error_message.str(),
4536  OOMPH_CURRENT_FUNCTION,
4537  OOMPH_EXCEPTION_LOCATION);
4538  }
4539 
4540  if (tang_dir_size == 2)
4541  {
4542  std::ostringstream warning_message;
4543  warning_message
4544  << "The spatial dimension is " << spatial_dimension << ".\n"
4545  << "I do not need a tangent direction vector to create \n"
4546  << "continuous tangent vectors in two spatial dimensions.";
4547  OomphLibWarning(warning_message.str(),
4548  OOMPH_CURRENT_FUNCTION,
4549  OOMPH_EXCEPTION_LOCATION);
4550 
4551  }
4552 #endif

4691  /// stored at the local nodes to i entries.
4692  void nbulk_value_resize(const unsigned &i) {Nbulk_value.resize(i);}
4693 
4694  /// \short Provide additional storage for a specified number of
4695  /// values at the nodes of the FaceElement. (This is needed, for
4696  /// instance, in free-surface elements, if the non-penetration
4697  /// condition is imposed by Lagrange multipliers whose values
4698  /// are only stored at the surface nodes but not in the interior of
4699  /// the bulk element). \c nadditional_data_values[n] specifies the
4700  /// number of additional values required at node \c n of the
4701  /// FaceElement. \b Note: Since this function is executed separately
4702  /// for each FaceElement, nodes that are common to multiple elements
4703  /// might be resized repeatedly. To avoid this, we only allow
4704  /// a single resize operation by comparing the number of values stored
4705  /// at each node to the number of values the node had when it
4706  /// was simply a member of the associated "bulk"
4707  /// element. <b>There are cases where this will break!</b> -- e.g. if
4708  /// a node is common to two FaceElements which require
4709  /// additional storage for distinct quantities. Such cases
4710  /// need to be handled by "hand-crafted" face elements.
4711  void resize_nodes(Vector<unsigned> &nadditional_data_values)
4712  {
4713  //Locally cache the number of node
4714  unsigned n_node = nnode();
4715  //Resize the storage for values at the nodes:
4716  for (unsigned l=0; l<n_node; l++)
4717  {
4718  //Find number of values stored at the node
4719  unsigned Initial_Nvalue = node_pt(l)->nvalue();
4720  //Read out the number of additional values
4721  unsigned Nadditional = nadditional_data_values[l];
4722  //If the node has not already been resized, resize it
4723  if ((Initial_Nvalue == Nbulk_value[l]) && (Nadditional > 0))
4724  {
4725  //Resize the node according to the number of additional values
4726  node_pt(l)->resize(Nbulk_value[l]+Nadditional);
4727  }
4728  } //End of loop over nodes
4729  }
4730 
4731  /// Output boundary coordinate zeta
4732  void output_zeta(std::ostream &outfile, const unsigned& nplot);
4733 
4734  };

4738  //========================================================================
4739  /// SolidFaceElements combine FaceElements and SolidFiniteElements
4740  /// and overload various functions so they work properly in the
4741  /// FaceElement context
4742  //========================================================================
4743  class SolidFaceElement: public virtual FaceElement,
4744  public virtual SolidFiniteElement
4745  {
4746 
4747  public:
4748 
4749  /// \short The "global" intrinsic coordinate of the element when
4750  /// viewed as part of a geometric object should be given by
4751  /// the FaceElement representation, by default
4752  /// This final over-ride is required because both SolidFiniteElements
4753  /// and FaceElements overload zeta_nodal
4754  double zeta_nodal(const unsigned &n, const unsigned &k,
4755  const unsigned &i) const
4756  {return FaceElement::zeta_nodal(n,k,i);}
4757 
4758 
4759 
4760  /// \short Return i-th FE-interpolated Lagrangian coordinate xi[i] at
4761  /// local coordinate s. Overloaded from SolidFiniteElement. Note that
4762  /// the Lagrangian coordinates are those defined in the bulk!
4763  /// For instance, in a 1D FaceElement that is aligned with
4764  /// the Lagrangian coordinate line xi_0=const, only xi_1 will vary
4765  /// in the FaceElement. This may confuse you if you (wrongly!) believe that
4766  /// in a 1D SolidElement there should only a single Lagrangian
4767  /// coordinate, namely xi_0!
4768  double interpolated_xi(const Vector<double> &s,
4769  const unsigned &i) const
4770  {
4771  // Local coordinates in bulk element
4772  Vector<double> s_bulk(dim()+1);
4773  s_bulk=local_coordinate_in_bulk(s);
4774 
4775  // Return Lagrangian coordinate as computed by bulk
4776  return dynamic_cast<SolidFiniteElement*>(bulk_element_pt())->
4777  interpolated_xi(s_bulk,i);
4778  }
4779 
4780 
4781  /// \short Compute FE interpolated Lagrangian coordinate vector xi[] at
4782  /// local coordinate s as Vector. Overloaded from SolidFiniteElement. Note
4783  /// that the Lagrangian coordinates are those defined in the bulk!
4784  /// For instance, in a 1D FaceElement that is aligned with
4785  /// the Lagrangian coordinate line xi_0=const, only xi_1 will vary
4786  /// in the FaceElement. This may confuse you if you (wrongly!) believe that
4787  /// in a 1D SolidElement there should only a single Lagrangian
4788  /// coordinate, namely xi_0!
4789  void interpolated_xi(const Vector<double> &s,
4790  Vector<double>& xi) const
4791  {
4792  // Local coordinates in bulk element
4793  Vector<double> s_bulk(dim()+1);
4794  s_bulk=local_coordinate_in_bulk(s);
4795 
4796  // Get Lagrangian position vector
4797  dynamic_cast<SolidFiniteElement*>(bulk_element_pt())->
4798  interpolated_xi(s_bulk,xi);
4799  }
4800 
4801 
4802  };
